	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Johannesburg - The Johannesburg home of Communications Minister Ayanda Dlodlo was broken into in the early hours on Monday morning. GCIS said in a statement that an intruder gained access to the home. "The ministry would like to assure the nation that Minister Dlodlo and her family are safe and unharmed," it said. "The minister has reported the matter to the police and the investigation is underway." More to follow.  24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  